    <keyword>kron</keyword>
    <short_description>Kronecker tensor product.</short_description>
    <syntax>
        <syntax_item>K = kron(A, B)</syntax_item>
    </syntax>
    <param_input>
        <param_input_item>
            <param_name>A</param_name>
            <param_description
      >a matrix: scalars, vectors or matrices.</param_description>
        </param_input_item>
        <param_input_item>
            <param_name>B</param_name>
            <param_description
      >a matrix: scalars, vectors or matrices.</param_description>
        </param_input_item>
    </param_input>
    <param_output>
        <param_output_item>
            <param_name>K</param_name>
            <param_description
      >result: Kronecker Tensor Product.</param_description>
        </param_output_item>
    </param_output>
    <description>
        <p>
            <b
      >K = kron(A, B)</b> computes the Kronecker tensor product of matrices <b
      >A</b> and <b>B</b>.
        </p>
        <p>For matrices</p>
        <latex>A</latex>
        <p>of size</p>
        <latex>m \times n</latex>
        <p>and</p>
        <latex>B</latex>
        <p>of size</p>
        <latex>p \times q</latex>
        <p>, the Kronecker product is:</p>
        <latex>A \otimes B = \begin{pmatrix} 
        a_{11}B &amp; a_{12}B &amp; \cdots &amp; a_{1n}B \\
        a_{21}B &amp; a_{22}B &amp; \cdots &amp; a_{2n}B \\
        \vdots &amp; \vdots &amp; \ddots &amp; \vdots \\
        a_{m1}B &amp; a_{m2}B &amp; \cdots &amp; a_{mn}B 
        \end{pmatrix}</latex>
        <p>The result is an</p>
        <latex>mp \times nq</latex>
        <p>matrix.</p>
    </description>
    <bibliography>https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kronecker_product</bibliography>
